OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FHow WW2 captives found a   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fglint of light to live     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, During World War Two, hundreds of      
OL,6, thousands of people were held against  
OL,7, their will. Service personnel captured 
OL,8, in conflict became prisoners of war,   
OL,9, and civilians were confined in         
OL,10, internment camps if they were believed 
OL,11, to be a threat to the state.           
OL,13,FThe exploits of the people who managed 
OL,14,Fto physically escape are often         
OL,15,Fwell-known, their extraordinary stories
OL,16,Fimmortalised in film, literature and   
OL,17,Fpublic memory.                         
OL,19,FBut lesser known are the people who    
OL,20,Falso found a path to a form of escape, 
OL,21,Fbut within their own minds.            
